[69.11219, "o", "======================================================================\r\nDST Bug Fix Verification\r\n======================================================================\r\n\r\nMeeting: Maintenance Window Prep\r\nStored UTC time: 2024-03-31T01:30:00\r\nExpected Berlin time: 2024-03-31 03:30:00 CEST (UTC+2)\r\n\r\nNote: March 31, 2024 is DST transition day in Europe/Berlin"]
[69.112284, "o", "\r\nAt 2:00 AM CET, clocks jump forward to 3:00 AM CEST\r\n\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nOLD BUGGY BEHAVIOR:\r\n"]
[69.118292, "o", "Result: 2024-03-31 01:30:00 CET+0100\r\n✗ WRONG: Treated UTC time as Berlin time, giving 1:30\r\n\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------"]
[69.118324, "o", "\r\nNEW FIXED BEHAVIOR:\r\n"]
[69.118355, "o", "Result: 2024-03-31 03:30:00 CEST+0200\r\n✓ CORRECT: Properly converted UTC to Berlin time (3:30 CEST)\r\n\r\n======================================================================\r\n"]
[69.118391, "o", "IMPACT: With the bug, reminders would be sent 1 hour early/late\r\nduring DST transitions, causing the exact issue reported.\r\n======================================================================\r\n"]
[69.122563, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[69.122593, "o", "user@2a422e2e1198:~/scheduler$ "]
[84.971013, "i", "cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\n# DST Bug Fix Summary\n\n## Problem\nThe scheduler app was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times (off by 1 hour) for meetings between 2am-3am local time in Europe/Berlin timezone. This occurred specifically during DST (Daylight Saving Time) transitions.\n\n## Root Cause\nIn `/home/user/scheduler/app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug:\n\n```python\n# BUGGY CODE (line 30):\nberlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)\n```\n\nThis incorrectly treated the UTC datetime as if it were already in Berlin time, rather than converting FROM UTC TO Berlin time.\n\n## The Fix\nChanged the conversion to properly handle timezone conversion:\n\n```python\n# FIXED CODE (lines 29-32):\n# First, localize as UTC (since the input is UTC)\nutc_dt = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)\n\n# Then convert to Berlin time\nberlin_dt = utc_dt.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)\n```\n\n## Impact\n- **Before**: 2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC → 01:30 CET (WRONG)\n- **After**: 2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC → 03:30 CEST (CORRECT)\n\nThe Monday 2:30am "]
[84.971133, "i", "maintenance window reminder will now be sent at the correct time.\n\n## Files Modified\n- `/home/user/scheduler/app.py` - Fixed timezone conversion logic\n- `/home/user/scheduler/app.py.backup` - Backup of original buggy version\n\n## Testing\nRun `python3 /home/user/scheduler/test_fix.py` to verify the fix works correctly.\nRun `python3 /home/user/scheduler/verify_fix.py` to see before/after comparison.\nEOF\n"]
[84.971184, "o", "cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\r\n"]
